\
\f1\b\fs28\li2200 isEqual:\f0\b0\
\f0\fs28\li2500 - (BOOL){\b isEqual}:{\i attrib}\fs16\
\
\f0\fs28\li2200 The equality test for TextAttributes is used by RunArray's {\f2 coalesce} method to merge adjacent TextAttribute instances.\fs16\
\
\fs16\
\
\f1\b\fs28\li2200 dominates:\f0\b0\
\f0\fs28\li2500 - (BOOL){\b dominates}:{\i attrib}\fs16\
\
\f0\fs28\li2200 Should return YES if the receiver dominates {\i attrib}.  This implies that, when the receiver is added to a list of Text Attributes, attributes that are dominated by the receiver will be removed.\fs16\
\
\f0\fs28\li2200 The default returns NO, unless both objects are members of the same class and equal to each other (in which case they don't need to be added more than once to the attribute list). \fs16\
\
\fs16\
\
\f1\b\fs28\li2200 reset\f0\b0\
\f0\fs28\li2500 -{\b reset}\fs16\
\
\f0\fs28\li2200 Message that is sent to the attribute before it is added to a list of attributes.  Doesn't do anything by default.\fs16\
\
\fs16\
\
\f1\b\fs28\li2200 set\f0\b0\
\f0\fs28\li2500 - (BOOL){\b set}\fs16\
\
\f0\fs28\li2200 Message that is sent to the attribute before it is added to a list of attributes.  If it returns YES (the default), the attribute will be added.  May be overridden to {\i turn off} attributes.\fs16\
\
\fs16\
\
\f1\b\fs28\li2200 emphasizeScanner:\f0\b0\
\f0\fs28\li2500 -{\b emphasizeScanner}:{\i aScanner}\fs16\
\
\f0\fs28\li2200 The default implementation of this method simply returns {\b self}.\fs16\
\
\f0\fs28\li2200 Normally a {\i scanner} class (which renders text in some specific format) would send {\f2 emphasizeScanner:} messages with itself as argument to a list of text attributes.  The text attributes can then {\i act} upon the scanner and set text color, font and other formatting properties.\fs16\
